changelog=0.2.12: Optimized repeated cached scans for large folders. Cached scans now batch file-state replacement per task instead of rewriting state.json once per unchanged file, so large repeated scans avoid both recursive pCloud listing and thousands of full JSON writes.<br>0.2.11: Refined sync task card states and repeated scan caching. New tasks now show Not Scanned instead of Completed, full reconciliation shows Scanning, upload and queue work shows Syncing, and Completed is only shown after the task has file state with no pending work. Repeated scans now reuse cached synced/existing file state when the task path has not changed, avoiding another recursive pCloud listing after a successful sync.<br>0.2.10: Fixed task schedule field visibility in Settings. The UI now enforces the HTML hidden attribute in CSS so interval, daily, weekly, and manual schedules actually hide fields that do not apply. Manual scans with no enabled tasks now show a no-task message instead of saying the scan was triggered.<br>0.2.9: Simplified Settings and Sync Logs. The global scan interval field was removed from Sync Rules, each task schedule now only shows fields that apply to the selected mode, and the separate Event column was removed from Sync Logs.<br>0.2.8: Scheduled runs now drain a local filesystem watcher queue instead of rescanning every task directory. Manual scans still perform full local and pCloud reconciliation, startup no longer triggers an automatic full scan, and watcher-unavailable tasks fall back to full scans with a watch_failed log event.<br>0.2.7: Sync runs now use a task queue so each task scans and uploads before the next task starts. The dashboard shows the current task metrics while a task is running, task cards show per-task counts, and each task can be scheduled manually, by interval, daily, or weekly.<br>0.2.6: Initial takeover of existing pCloud folders now treats same-path same-size remote files as Existing even when pCloud mtimes differ, while later same-size local changes still upload by using previous scan metadata. Scan completion events now include the remote file count.<br>0.2.5: Manual and scheduled scans now rebuild file state from the current task set, clearing stale pending and failed records from previous tasks, and add a separate Existing metric for files already present in pCloud.<br>0.2.4: Removed the default pCloud root setting from the UI, made each task pCloud folder the exact remote destination, opened the remote picker from root when no folder is selected, and added Stop Sync to abort active uploads back to pending.<br>0.2.3: Added file size and active upload progress to Sync Logs, fixed unrealistic upload speed spikes, and bound the raw app port to host loopback by default so unauthenticated APIs stay behind the fnOS reverse proxy.<br>0.2.2: Added configurable sync log retention by age and count, plus a one-click log delete action. Settings now shows task configuration first, moves less common pCloud authorization and sync rules below it, documents that pCloud official upload docs do not publish a recommended concurrency number, and removes the decorative window dots and sidebar brand text.<br>0.2.1: Bumped the package version for fnOS installation and upgrade detection. Sync logs now focus on file-level upload results, task cards are compact, saved access tokens show a masked value in the UI, and deleting all tasks also clears migrated legacy sources.<br>0.2.0: Added multi-task upload jobs, sidebar navigation, local folder picker, pCloud remote folder picker, remote folder creation, aggregate upload speed, and pCloud API integrations for getapiserver, currentserver, uploadprogress, checksumfile, and diff.<br>0.1.9: Reworked sync logs as a filterable table, added per-file success records, and drained the pending queue after retrying failed or stuck files.<br>0.1.8: Fixed stuck uploading records when no failures were visible, and exposed running version plus uploading file details in the status API and UI.<br>0.1.7: Added rsync-like remote comparison so unchanged cloud files are skipped while missing or changed files are uploaded, and cleaned up old dashed state.<br>0.1.6: Recovered interrupted uploads that stayed in uploading state, and migrated old dashed remote directory names to normalized directories.<br>0.1.5: Preserved non-ASCII source folder names instead of converting them to dashed remote folders, with migration for old dashed configuration.<br>0.1.4: Created remote directories parent-first, serialized state saves, and added Content-Length plus transient socket retry handling for uploads.<br>0.1.3: Fixed pCloud OAuth access token API calls to use access_token.<br>0.1.2: Switched the default base image to an explicit mirror-friendly Node image.<br>0.1.1: Made the Node base image configurable to avoid public registry pull failures.<br>0.1.0: Initial one-way upload sync with pCloud OAuth, folder configuration, status counters, and failed-file retry.
